{"article_id":"IZqWFLzNpVkQodKI","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The internet","depth":10},{"id":1,"text":"as we know it","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"is about to change drastically .","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"Net neutrality","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"- the standard","depth":12},{"id":5,"text":"that internet service providers , or ISPs , must treat all traffic equally -","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"was repealed Thursday in a party-line vote by the Federal Communications Commission in Washington .","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"FCC chair Ajit Pai ,","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"flanked by two Republican allies ,","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"has a majority on the commission .","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"Commercial ISPs like Comcast , AT & T , and Verizon will be free to block content , throttle users ' internet use ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"and prioritize their own services at the expense of competitors ' .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"It ' s a wide-reaching and controversial issue","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that some have called one of the \" biggest corporate giveaways in history . \"","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"As net neutrality proponents see it ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"these protections are essential","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"to providing open and equal access to the internet .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"The plan by Pai , a former Verizon attorney , is a wide-ranging dismantling of not only the safeguards","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"put in place by the Obama administration","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"but ones","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"that have been embedded in the World Wide Web since its invention in 1989 .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"Pai maintains","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"that his proposal is a standard rollback in government regulation","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"that gives ISPs more freedom for things like infrastructure investments .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"But critics argue","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"that this would result in fast and slow lanes for internet access","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"and could lead to favoritism and the entrenchment of wealthy players .","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"In other words , nothing could stop AT & T from slowing down Netflix in an effort","depth":13},{"id":28,"text":"to prioritize its own cable TV package ,","depth":13},{"id":29,"text":"or outright blocking a website","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"that ' s critical of its business practices .","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"To better understand what ' s at stake ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"I spoke to Barbara van Schewick , a net neutrality expert and a professor at Stanford Law School , before the vote .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"The conversation has been lightly edited","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"and condensed .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"Why should ordinary people care about net neutrality ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"which can seem very complicated ?","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"The internet is n't a specialized service for geeks anymore .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"It 's long become woven into everyone 's daily lives and every sector of the economy .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"Net neutrality is the secret sauce","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"that has made the internet awesome .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"It ensures","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"that we , not Comcast or Verizon , get to choose what content we read , what websites","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"we go to , and what services","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"we use on the internet .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"That 's been the case since the beginning of the internet in the US ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"and it has stayed that way","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"because the FCC , under the leadership of Democrats and Republicans alike , ensured","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"that the companies","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"we pay","depth":14},{"id":50,"text":"to get online","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"could not interfere with the free markets and free marketplaces of ideas .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"Pai 's proposal will change that .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"It will allow broadband providers to block websites on content grounds ,","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"decide which apps","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"we can use ,","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"charge online services","depth":15},{"id":57,"text":"simply to reach subscribers at all ,","depth":15},{"id":58,"text":"create fast lanes","depth":16},{"id":59,"text":"that favor companies and speakers with deep pockets ,","depth":16},{"id":60,"text":"and make it more expensive for local and niche sites to reach readers .","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"Americans understand this .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"That ' s why Pai 's move","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"to abolish net neutrality protections","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"that date [ to ] long before 2015","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"has led to such a loud and sustained outcry by Americans of all political affiliations .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"Americans filed millions of comments with the FCC ,","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"even more","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"than were filed in 2014 .","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"Startups , small businesses , investors , faith groups , musicians , and community activists have filed comments ,","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"held rallies ,","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"written op-eds ,","depth":15},{"id":72,"text":"and called","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"and met with their members of Congress .","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"Americans have placed more than 1 million calls to Congress","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"urging","depth":16},{"id":76,"text":"that the protections stay in place ,","depth":16},{"id":77,"text":"and that 's just through BattleForTheNet.com alone .","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"If net neutrality protections are stripped ,","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"ISPs in theory would have the right","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"to block any website or content","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"they see fit , even a newspaper","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"whose editorials it doesn ' t like .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"But do you think","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"that 's something","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"they would ever do ?","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"That ISPs would go that far ?","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"Blocking and throttling , like how Comcast once restricted the peer-to-peer file sharing application BitTorrent , really is a concern .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"[ And","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"while P2P programs have been stigmatized as a means","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"for distributing copyrighted materials ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"it ' s also become a popular protocol","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"for sharing things like open source operating systems and other large legal files . ]","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"The regime","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"that Pai is now proposing ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"which is that the Federal Trade Commission will now police ISPs","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"- that ' s putting our internet under an agency","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"that has no rules against blocking or discrimination .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"The only protection","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"that will remain","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"is the rule","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"that says","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"if you block or discriminate ,","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"or you offer \" paid pass lanes \" to websites","depth":16},{"id":104,"text":"[ that is , solicit payments for faster service ] ,","depth":16},{"id":105,"text":"then you have to tell your customers about it .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"The markets for internet access in Europe are a lot more competitive than the markets in the United States .","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"Here , 51 percent of Americans only have one ISP","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"to choose from .","depth":15},{"id":109,"text":"So those people have no other option","depth":15},{"id":110,"text":"if they don ' t like how their ISP is behaving .","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"But Europe has a lot more competition","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"because they require the phone companies to open their networks to independent ISPs .","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"So the Europeans said ,","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"`` We think","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"net neutrality is a problem","depth":16},{"id":116,"text":"that can be fixed with competition . ''","depth":16},{"id":117,"text":"So","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"if ISPs said to customers","depth":17},{"id":119,"text":"that they are blocking or slowing down websites ,","depth":17},{"id":120,"text":"then customers","depth":18},{"id":121,"text":"who do n't like that","depth":18},{"id":122,"text":"can go to another ISP","depth":18},{"id":123,"text":"that does n't do the same .","depth":18},{"id":124,"text":"And this threat","depth":17},{"id":125,"text":"of people","depth":18},{"id":126,"text":"switching providers","depth":18},{"id":127,"text":"would discipline the ISPs","depth":16},{"id":128,"text":"and ultimately prevent blocking and discrimination .","depth":15},{"id":129,"text":"That won ' t work in the US ,","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"and it didn ' t in Europe .","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"And that 's exactly the rhetoric","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"Pai is using :","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"that competition will keep ISPs honest .","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"So that 's his argument .","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"And it sounds really nice in theory ,","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"but it does n't work in practice","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"because there are so few ISPs available to many people in the US .","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"We know that","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"because the European Union ran this experiment for us .","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"After they adopted their regime ,","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"they had widespread blocking and discrimination","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"[ even with the additional competition ] .","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"Looking to Europe ,","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"we can see what a world without net neutrality looks like .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"In the Netherlands , the telecommunication company KPN was losing a lot of money","depth":16},{"id":146,"text":"because so many people were using online text messaging apps like WhatsApp .","depth":16},{"id":147,"text":"People were n't paying for the traditional , expensive text messages over a cellular network .","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"KPN said ,","depth":17},{"id":149,"text":"`` We are losing all this money .","depth":18},{"id":150,"text":"That 's not sustainable .","depth":18},{"id":151,"text":"We will switch to plans","depth":17},{"id":152,"text":"that do not include the right","depth":18},{"id":153,"text":"to use online text messaging . ''","depth":18},{"id":154,"text":"And","depth":16},{"id":155,"text":"if someone wanted to use online text messaging ,","depth":17},{"id":156,"text":"they had to buy an online text messaging option .","depth":17},{"id":157,"text":"That got such a huge outcry in the Netherlands","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"that they became the first country","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"to adopt a net neutrality law","depth":16},{"id":160,"text":"that banned blocking and slowing down and speeding up websites .","depth":16},{"id":161,"text":"And we had a German ISP","depth":15},{"id":162,"text":"that blocked access to websites","depth":16},{"id":163,"text":"that were criticizing its business practices .","depth":16},{"id":164,"text":"We have never seen this in the US","depth":16},{"id":165,"text":"because under our net neutrality regime , that would n't be legal .","depth":17},{"id":166,"text":"Our regime says","depth":18},{"id":167,"text":"an ISP can not block legal content , applications , and services .","depth":18},{"id":168,"text":"That means","depth":16},{"id":169,"text":"if it 's legal ,","depth":17},{"id":170,"text":"the ISP ca n't block it .","depth":17},{"id":171,"text":"Let 's say","depth":15},{"id":172,"text":"we do n't like online gun sales or whatever it is .","depth":15},{"id":173,"text":"The ISP can only say ,","depth":15},{"id":174,"text":"`` Look","depth":17},{"id":175,"text":"I ca n't do anything about it ,","depth":17},{"id":176,"text":"because","depth":17},{"id":177,"text":"as long as it 's legal ,","depth":18},{"id":178,"text":"we have to transmit it . ''","depth":18},{"id":179,"text":"A lot of ISPs have been touting their own net neutrality pledges","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"and saying","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"even if these regulations are stripped ,","depth":14},{"id":183,"text":"they will still abide by net neutrality guidelines .","depth":14},{"id":184,"text":"But Comcast , for instance , recently deleted their original net neutrality pledge the same day","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"the FCC announced its first draft","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"to appeal these regulations .","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"And then the new one","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"they put up","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"contained no promise","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"related to not engaging in paid priority .","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"Can we take these corporate pledges seriously ?","depth":9},{"id":192,"text":"I would not want the future of the internet to depend on an ISP 's willingness","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"to voluntarily behave in a good way .","depth":10},{"id":194,"text":"We have seen in Europe","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"that it 's not necessarily in the ISP 's interest to behave in the way","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"that 's required by net neutrality .","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"And ISPs can change their promises ,","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"and already the promises are so much narrower than what the net neutrality protections require .","depth":14},{"id":199,"text":"None of the ISPs talk about a promise","depth":15},{"id":200,"text":"to manage networks in a way","depth":16},{"id":201,"text":"that does not single out applications or classes of applications .","depth":16},{"id":202,"text":"None of them commit to not charging websites for access .","depth":14},{"id":203,"text":"These are essential components for net neutrality ,","depth":11},{"id":204,"text":"and so I do not think at all","depth":11},{"id":205,"text":"that we should leave the future of this really critical infrastructure to promises by the ISPs","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"that can change at any time .","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"Pai has claimed","depth":7},{"id":208,"text":"that the real threat to the open internet is from social media companies like Twitter","depth":7},{"id":209,"text":"because it moderates","depth":7},{"id":210,"text":"and has removed conservative content from its platform .","depth":7},{"id":211,"text":"Do you think","depth":6},{"id":212,"text":"there ' s any truth there ?","depth":6},{"id":213,"text":"I think","depth":7},{"id":214,"text":"that 's really just an effort","depth":8},{"id":215,"text":"to distract people .","depth":8},{"id":216,"text":"I know","depth":9},{"id":217,"text":"there are a lot of people","depth":11},{"id":218,"text":"who are unhappy with the specific way","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"in which companies like Twitter or Google or Facebook manage their services","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"and how they limit certain content on their site .","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"We can have a long debate about that .","depth":8},{"id":222,"text":"But there is a key difference between the website","depth":10},{"id":223,"text":"that runs on top of the internet","depth":10},{"id":224,"text":"and the actual internet .","depth":9},{"id":225,"text":"And the difference is ,","depth":10},{"id":226,"text":"if a website blocks certain content ,","depth":11},{"id":227,"text":"I can go to a different website .","depth":11},{"id":228,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":229,"text":"if my ISP blocks access to a certain website ,","depth":11},{"id":230,"text":"then there 's no way","depth":12},{"id":231,"text":"to get around that .","depth":12},{"id":232,"text":"And I think","depth":6},{"id":233,"text":"part of what was so surprising about Pai using this example is because","depth":7},{"id":234,"text":"if people are concerned and unhappy","depth":10},{"id":235,"text":"that companies like Twitter or other internet platform companies are policing certain content on their sites ,","depth":10},{"id":236,"text":"these people should really be fighting for net neutrality protections .","depth":9},{"id":237,"text":"They are the only thing","depth":9},{"id":238,"text":"that prevents the ISPs from engaging in the same behavior .","depth":9},{"id":239,"text":"The debate about net neutrality has been increasingly cast as a liberal versus conservative issue .","depth":4},{"id":240,"text":"Do you think","depth":5},{"id":241,"text":"that ' s a good or bad thing","depth":6},{"id":242,"text":"for protecting the open internet ?","depth":6},{"id":243,"text":"It 's really misleading .","depth":6},{"id":244,"text":"Net neutrality is n't a partisan issue .","depth":8},{"id":245,"text":"Polls consistently show","depth":10},{"id":246,"text":"that Americans ,","depth":12},{"id":247,"text":"whether Republican or Democrat ,","depth":12},{"id":248,"text":"support the current net neutrality protections .","depth":11},{"id":249,"text":"A poll","depth":12},{"id":250,"text":"that was published in July","depth":12},{"id":251,"text":"shows","depth":11},{"id":252,"text":"that 77 percent of Americans support the current protections at the FCC","depth":12},{"id":253,"text":"- and that 73 percent of Republicans , 80 percent of Democrats , and 76 percent of independents want to keep the current protections .","depth":12},{"id":254,"text":"And","depth":12},{"id":255,"text":"if you look on some of the more conservative subreddits on Reddit or even Breitbart ,","depth":13},{"id":256,"text":"there was huge , vibrant opposition to Pai 's plan .","depth":13},{"id":257,"text":"Net neutrality protections are absolutely consistent with a free market framework .","depth":8},{"id":258,"text":"They are really a way","depth":9},{"id":259,"text":"to protect all these free markets","depth":10},{"id":260,"text":"that arose from and depend on the internet .","depth":10},{"id":261,"text":"Tim Wu , the Columbia professor","depth":9},{"id":262,"text":"who coined the term \" net neutrality , \"","depth":9},{"id":263,"text":"has argued","depth":8},{"id":264,"text":"that the judiciary will in the end have to save net neutrality .","depth":7},{"id":265,"text":"You , on the other hand , advocated in a piece","depth":8},{"id":266,"text":"that Congress should intervene .","depth":8},{"id":267,"text":"Do you think","depth":9},{"id":268,"text":"there ' s still a chance","depth":10},{"id":269,"text":"to stop the FCC order","depth":11},{"id":270,"text":"before it ' s adopted ,","depth":11},{"id":271,"text":"and what do you fear","depth":9},{"id":272,"text":"will happen","depth":10},{"id":273,"text":"if it isn ' t ?","depth":10},{"id":274,"text":"Wu is right","depth":7},{"id":275,"text":"that the FCC ' s draft order is based on a shaky legal foundation","depth":8},{"id":276,"text":"and is likely to be struck down in court .","depth":8},{"id":277,"text":"But that shouldn ' t have made people complacent in the first place .","depth":6},{"id":278,"text":"And the hope is","depth":7},{"id":279,"text":"Congress would have intervened before this ruling .","depth":7},{"id":280,"text":"Up until the vote , there is still a chance","depth":8},{"id":281,"text":"to stop the order in the first place .","depth":8},{"id":282,"text":"[ If it passes ] ,","depth":9},{"id":283,"text":"it will immediately cause uncertainty for angel investors and venture capitalists ,","depth":10},{"id":284,"text":"chilling their investments in startups .","depth":10},{"id":285,"text":"Then","depth":10},{"id":286,"text":"when the order goes into effect ,","depth":12},{"id":287,"text":"after being published in the Federal Register ,","depth":12},{"id":288,"text":"broadband providers will be free to start charging fees for access to users and pay-to-play fast lanes .","depth":11},{"id":289,"text":"Even if a court stays the order ,","depth":10},{"id":290,"text":"the uncertainty for investors will remain .","depth":10},{"id":291,"text":"Eric Allen Been is a freelance writer","depth":2},{"id":292,"text":"who has written for the Wall Street Journal , the Boston Globe , Vice , Playboy , the New Republic , the Los Angeles Review of Books , and TheAtlantic.com .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":585,"left":583,"right":584,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":583,"left":531,"right":582,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":531,"left":499,"right":530,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":499,"left":327,"right":498,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":327,"left":323,"right":326,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":323,"left":306,"right":322,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":302,"right":305,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":295,"right":301,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":294,"right":2,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":294,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":298,"right":300,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":298,"left":297,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":3,"right":296,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":299,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":299,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":305,"left":303,"right":304,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":304,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":322,"left":308,"right":321,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":308,"left":14,"right":307,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":307,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":321,"left":311,"right":320,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":311,"left":309,"right":310,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":309,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":310,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":320,"left":313,"right":319,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":313,"left":21,"right":312,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":312,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":319,"left":24,"right":318,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":318,"left":314,"right":317,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":314,"left":25,"right":26,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":317,"left":315,"right":316,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":315,"left":27,"right":28,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":316,"left":29,"right":30,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":326,"left":324,"right":325,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":324,"left":31,"right":32,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":325,"left":33,"right":34,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":498,"left":369,"right":497,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":369,"left":330,"right":368,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":330,"left":328,"right":329